cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.MM 

This paper deals with privacy concerns related to online tracking and ad exchanges, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The methodology developed in the paper involves analyzing ad impressions and identifying information flows between ad exchanges, which involves techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR) and data management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses how the findings can be used to give users more control over their data, which relates to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves analyzing ad content and user behavior, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
